Halve peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Remove the ends from the @carrot{1}(trimmed, no need to peel), thinly slice into rounds. Trim the @green beans{150%g} and chop into 3 pieces. Trim the @spring onion{1}, thinly slice. Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{1%drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on high heat. Once hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until charred and tender, ~{4-6%minutes}. Remove to a #bowl{} once charred.

Pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}. Stir in the @jasmine rice{150} and @salt{1/4%tsp}, cover with the lid and bring to the boil on medium-high heat. Once boiling, turn the heat down to its lowest setting. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While the rice cooks, pop the @panko breadcrumbs{10} into a bowl. Add the @water for the breadcrumbs{2%tbsp}, the lime zest and the @Thai style spice mix{1%tsp} (add less if you don't like heat). Mix together and add the @British pork mince{240%g}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Using your hands, mix everything together until very well combined. Form the mixture into evenly sized balls, 5 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Once the green beans are removed, pop your frying pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil. Once hot, add the meatballs and fry until browned on the outside, ~{5-6%minutes}. Turn every ~{2%minutes}. Remove to a #plate{} (we'll finish cooking them later).

Pop your frying pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil if the pan is dry. Add the carrot and shallot to the pan and season with salt and pepper. Fry, stirring frequently until the veg is soft, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the @red Thai style paste{50%g} to the carrot and shallot, stir very well, cook for ~{1%minute}, then add in the meatballs and pour in the @coconut milk{200%ml} and @water for the sauce{150%ml}. Add the @chicken stock paste{10%g} and season with salt and pepper. Bring to the boil, simmer until the sauce has thickened and the meatballs are cooked, ~{6-7%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the curry is cooked, stir in the charred beans and cook for ~{1%minute}.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Remove the pan from the heat, squeeze in half the lime juice, then taste and add more lime juice, salt and pepper if you feel it needs it.

Fluff up the rice and spoon into #bowls{}. Top with the curry, sprinkle over the spring onion and enjoy!